  "aboutPageTitle": "About",
  "aboutTabIntroLabel": "Overview",
  "aboutTabIntroHeroTitle": "Keep your private diary in your own hands",
  "aboutTabIntroHeroBody": "Quill Diary is a local, encrypted diary app for personal journaling. Your data stays on your device by default; create backups or exports when needed.",
  "aboutTabIntroChip0": "Data stays on device",
  "aboutTabIntroChip1": "Markdown export",
  "aboutTabIntroChip2": "Full-text search",
  "aboutTabIntroChip3": "Full encrypted backup",
  "aboutTabIntroChip4": "Portable export",
  "aboutTabIntroSection0Title": "Why it works well for journaling",
  "aboutTabIntroSection0Subtitle": "It is not just cloud notes with a new name. Privacy protection and everyday use are designed together.",
  "aboutTabIntroSection0Item0Title": "Encrypted local storage",
  "aboutTabIntroSection0Item0Body": "Entries, attachments, drafts, and the search index stay on your device under encryption or session protection. Nothing leaves the phone unless you back up or export.",
  "aboutTabIntroSection0Item1Title": "Start without signing up",
  "aboutTabIntroSection0Item1Body": "Daily writing works without accounts or remote servers. Use local diaries, search, and review without creating an account.",
  "aboutTabIntroSection0Item2Title": "Less collection, less distraction",
  "aboutTabIntroSection0Item2Body": "The app has no ads or tracking SDKs and does not upload diary plaintext to developer servers. Treat it as a private writing space focused on privacy.",
  "aboutTabIntroSection1Title": "How you can use it",
  "aboutTabIntroSection1Subtitle": "From capturing the moment to reviewing later, common features are designed around personal journaling.",
  "aboutTabIntroSection1Item0Title": "Write what you want to remember",
  "aboutTabIntroSection1Item0Body": "Supports titles, dates, tags, images, and general attachments. Start writing a new entry immediately or read before editing an existing one. Export to Markdown or HTML when needed.",
  "aboutTabIntroSection1Item1Title": "View your records from different angles",
  "aboutTabIntroSection1Item1Body": "The home screen offers list, calendar, tag, and overview views. Browse by time, revisit by date, or organize your life through tags and stats.",
  "aboutTabIntroSection1Item2Title": "Find what you wrote before",
  "aboutTabIntroSection1Item2Body": "After unlock, search titles, tags, and body text to revisit a memory, find a keyword, or quickly review a period of time.",
  "aboutTabIntroSection1Item3Title": "Turn reviews into shareable formats",
  "aboutTabIntroSection1Item3Body": "Create a full backup of the encrypted diary vault or export Markdown or HTML for reading, organizing, or moving content.",
  "aboutTabIntroSection2Title": "You stay in control of your data",
  "aboutTabIntroSection2Subtitle": "Backup, export, and unlock methods play different roles so you can keep your data and understand the risk boundaries.",
  "aboutTabIntroSection2Item0Title": "Trusted device and recovery key",
  "aboutTabIntroSection2Item0Body": "Use screen lock or biometrics for everyday access. When you change devices, restore, or lose trusted status, the recovery key is what restores access.",
  "aboutTabIntroSection2Item1Title": "Full backups preserve the encrypted vault",
  "aboutTabIntroSection2Item1Body": "A full backup preserves the entire encrypted vault for complete restore later. It is not a document you can open and read directly.",
  "aboutTabIntroSection2Item2Title": "Protect exported content yourself",
  "aboutTabIntroSection2Item2Body": "Markdown and HTML exports are good for reading, organizing, and moving content, but they are readable documents and no longer carry the same in-app encryption.",
  "aboutTabIntroSection3Title": "Open source and branding",
  "aboutTabIntroSection3Subtitle": "Review the source code and license terms, and understand branding boundaries clearly.",
  "aboutTabIntroSection3Item0Title": "Open source under AGPL-3.0",
  "aboutTabIntroSection3Item0Body": "Source code is released under GNU Affero General Public License v3.0, so product behavior and implementation can be publicly reviewed for transparency.",
  "aboutTabIntroSection3Item1Title": "Quill Diary branding",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionLabel": "Unlock and session",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionHeroTitle": "Balance convenience and data protection",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionHeroBody": "Quill Diary does not make you repeat the heaviest verification every time you switch away and back, but it also does not leave an unlocked session open forever. This page explains unlock methods, auto-lock, and when a recovery key is required.",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionChip0": "Biometrics",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionChip1": "Screen lock",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionChip2": "Auto-lock",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionChip3": "Recovery key",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionSection0Title": "Choosing an unlock method",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionSection0Subtitle": "Switch modes in Settings based on your device habits and desired protection level.",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionSection0Item0Title": "None",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionSection0Item0Body": "No extra verification after lock; the app resumes immediately. Suitable when no device screen lock is set, but offers the least protection.",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionSection0Item1Title": "Device screen lock",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionSection0Item1Body": "Re-verify with PIN, pattern, or password when returning to the app. Good if you want system-level protection without relying on biometrics.",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionSection0Item2Title": "Biometric verification",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionSection0Item2Body": "Prefer fingerprint or face verification, with screen lock as fallback on cancel or failure. Usually the most convenient option for daily use.",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionSection0Item3Title": "Shared requirements",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionSection0Item3Body": "Screen lock and biometric modes require a device screen lock first. Biometrics must also be enrolled in system settings.",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionSection1Title": "When re-verification happens",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionSection1Subtitle": "Diary entries, drafts, and the search index stay available only during a valid unlocked session.",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionSection1Item0Title": "While unlocked",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionSection1Item0Body": "While unlocked, you can read and write diaries, edit drafts, attach files, and use full-text search.",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionSection1Item1Title": "Background timeout",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionSection1Item2Title": "When returning to the app",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionSection1Item2Body": "A brief app switch usually does not trigger immediate re-verification. If the app stayed in the background longer than the timeout, your chosen mode decides whether it resumes directly or asks for system verification.",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionSection1Item3Title": "After cancelled or failed verification",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionSection1Item3Body": "If verification is cancelled or fails, the app stays locked without repeatedly prompting. Retry manually when convenient.",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionSection2Title": "Why a recovery key is still needed",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionSection2Subtitle": "Trusted devices offer convenience, but the recovery key is what truly restores access across devices and states.",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionSection2Item0Title": "After device change or reset",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionSection2Item0Body": "When you change phones, clear app data, or restore on another device, trusted device status usually does not carry over. The recovery key is required then.",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionSection2Item1Title": "When trusted status expires",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionSection2Item1Body": "If trusted status on the device expires or no longer matches the current vault state, local quick access alone is not enough.",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionSection2Item2Title": "Ultimate access credential",
  "aboutTabUnlockSessionSection2Item2Body": "The recovery key is not optional backup trivia. It is the required credential when changing devices, restoring, or losing trusted status. Keep it safe.",
  "aboutTabEncryptionLabel": "Encryption and decryption",
  "aboutTabEncryptionHeroTitle": "Data is stored encrypted by default",
  "aboutTabEncryptionHeroBody": "Quill Diary protects content before writing it into the diary vault. Entries, attachments, and other sensitive data use the LDJ2 format with AES-256-GCM encryption. Only the correct trusted-device or recovery-key path can open them.",
  "aboutTabEncryptionChip0": "Local encryption",
  "aboutTabEncryptionChip1": "LDJ2",
  "aboutTabEncryptionChip2": "AES-256-GCM",
  "aboutTabEncryptionChip3": "Argon2id",
  "aboutTabEncryptionChip4": "Trusted device",
  "aboutTabEncryptionChip5": "Android Keystore",
  "aboutTabEncryptionSection0Title": "What this protection does for you",
  "aboutTabEncryptionSection0Subtitle": "The point is not jargon. It is knowing that stored and read data follows a clear, consistent protection flow.",
  "aboutTabEncryptionSection0Item0Title": "LDJ2 + AES-256-GCM content protection",
  "aboutTabEncryptionSection0Item0Body": "Diary entries and attachments are wrapped in LDJ2 and encrypted with AES-256-GCM. Even if you see the file itself, the content is not directly readable.",
  "aboutTabEncryptionSection0Item1Title": "Tampering should fail immediately",
  "aboutTabEncryptionSection0Item1Body": "Stored data is encrypted and integrity-checked. If content or file headers are tampered with, decryption should fail instead of silently returning suspicious data.",
  "aboutTabEncryptionSection0Item2Title": "Each file has its own key",
  "aboutTabEncryptionSection0Item2Body": "Each encrypted file gets its own random file key, then vault-level protection wraps it. Different content does not share the same file key.",
  "aboutTabEncryptionSection1Title": "How you open your own data",
  "aboutTabEncryptionSection1Subtitle": "Everyday and emergency paths differ, but both end in the same decryption flow.",
  "aboutTabEncryptionSection1Item0Title": "Trusted device",
  "aboutTabEncryptionSection1Item0Body": "On a device with trusted status, daily access usually goes through screen lock or biometrics. Android Keystore protects important vault-layer keys on this path.",
  "aboutTabEncryptionSection1Item1Title": "Recovery key",
  "aboutTabEncryptionSection1Item1Body": "When you change devices, restore a backup, or lose local trusted status, the recovery key restores access to the entire vault after Argon2id derivation.",
  "aboutTabEncryptionSection1Item2Title": "Verify the vault first, then open each file",
  "aboutTabEncryptionSection1Item2Body": "The flow confirms current access can enter the vault correctly before opening individual files. This avoids mistaking wrong credentials for data corruption.",
  "aboutTabEncryptionSection2Title": "Boundaries to understand",
  "aboutTabEncryptionSection2Subtitle": "Encryption protects the vault itself, but not every situation is automatically safe.",
  "aboutTabEncryptionSection2Item0Title": "Exports are no longer the same protection layer",
  "aboutTabEncryptionSection2Item0Body": "Once you export to Markdown or HTML, storage and sharing risks for readable documents are no longer handled by in-app encryption.",
  "aboutTabEncryptionSection2Item1Title": "Keep your recovery key safe",
  "aboutTabEncryptionSection2Item1Body": "The recovery key is essential for re-entering the vault. If it leaks, is lost, or is not stored safely, security and recoverability may be affected.",
  "aboutTabEncryptionSection2Item2Title": "It protects data at rest",
  "aboutTabEncryptionSection2Item2Body": "This design mainly protects encrypted data stored on the device. If the device is compromised or someone obtains an unlocked session, risk depends on more than file format alone.",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexLabel": "Index and search",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexHeroTitle": "Find what you wrote quickly after unlock",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexHeroBody": "Search does not reread every diary entry each time. It uses an encrypted index for faster lookup. The index opens only while unlocked so search and protection can coexist.",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexChip0": "Title/body search",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexChip1": "Encrypted index",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexChip2": "Available while unlocked",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexChip3": "Rebuildable",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexSection0Title": "What search helps you find",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexSection0Subtitle": "Useful when reviewing, organizing, or narrowing down a memory quickly.",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexSection0Item0Title": "Search titles, tags, and body text",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexSection0Item0Body": "Search keywords in titles, body text, and tags without scrolling through every entry.",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexSection0Item1Title": "Results come from saved entries",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexSection0Item1Body": "Search shows content formally saved to the vault, not drafts still in the editor.",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexSection0Item2Title": "The index itself is protected",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexSection0Item2Body": "Search does not build a plaintext database on the side. It uses a separate encrypted index for speed.",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexSection1Title": "Why search does not slow daily use",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexSection1Subtitle": "Lookup work goes to the index layer instead of scanning every saved entry each time.",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexSection1Item0Title": "Index for speed",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexSection1Item0Body": "When you type a keyword, the system queries the index instead of decrypting the whole vault entry by entry.",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexSection1Item1Title": "Updates only after formal save",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexSection1Item1Body": "The index updates only after a successful save or import so results do not mix in uncertain drafts.",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexSection1Item2Title": "Can be rebuilt when needed",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexSection1Item2Body": "The index is derived data. After format updates, backup restore, or incompatible state, it is deleted and rebuilt.",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexSection2Title": "How it relates to security",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexSection2Subtitle": "Useful search does not mean giving up protection boundaries.",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexSection2Item0Title": "Available only while unlocked",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexSection2Item0Body": "The search index opens only during a valid unlocked session and closes when the app locks.",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexSection2Item1Title": "Drafts are not searchable",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexSection2Item1Body": "Drafts in progress do not appear in search results, avoiding unfinished content being treated as final records.",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexSection2Item2Title": "The vault remains the source of truth",
  "aboutTabSearchIndexSection2Item2Body": "The search index helps you find content faster. It does not replace the vault, which remains the authoritative source.",
  "aboutTabEditorLabel": "Diary editor",
  "aboutTabEditorHeroTitle": "Writing, drafts, and formal saves follow separate paths",
  "aboutTabEditorHeroBody": "The editor does not mix still writing with formally saved content. Changes go into encrypted drafts first, then update the saved entry and search index after you confirm save, making writing safer and easier to resume.",
  "aboutTabEditorChip0": "Markdown export",
  "aboutTabEditorChip1": "Image attachments",
  "aboutTabEditorChip2": "Auto drafts",
  "aboutTabEditorChip3": "Unsaved reminders",
  "aboutTabEditorSection0Title": "Everyday writing features",
  "aboutTabEditorSection0Subtitle": "Built around personal records, with common organization tools in one editing flow.",
  "aboutTabEditorSection0Item0Title": "Create or edit existing entries",
  "aboutTabEditorSection0Item0Body": "New entries open directly in edit mode. Existing ones can be read first and edited when you decide to change them.",
  "aboutTabEditorSection0Item1Title": "Content, title, date, and tags",
  "aboutTabEditorSection0Item1Body": "Edit diary content while organizing title, date, time, and tags. Formal save checks required fields to avoid incomplete records. Export to Markdown when needed.",
  "aboutTabEditorSection0Item2Title": "Images and general attachments",
  "aboutTabEditorSection0Item2Body": "Add multiple images or general files and reorder images. Diaries can preserve more than text by keeping context and materials from the moment.",
  "aboutTabEditorSection1Title": "Draft mechanism",
  "aboutTabEditorSection1Subtitle": "Drafts are not a minor extra. They are an important protection layer in the writing experience.",
  "aboutTabEditorSection1Item0Title": "Changes auto-save",
  "aboutTabEditorSection1Item0Body": "After entering edit mode, changes to title, date, tags, body, or attachments auto-save as encrypted drafts to reduce loss if interrupted.",
  "aboutTabEditorSection1Item1Title": "Restore when reopening",
  "aboutTabEditorSection1Item1Body": "When reopening the same entry or unfinished new content, if a local draft remains, the app asks whether to continue where you left off.",
  "aboutTabEditorSection1Item2Title": "Auto cleanup after formal save",
  "aboutTabEditorSection1Item2Body": "After content is formally saved to the vault, drafts are cleared. If you cancel editing without new changes, old drafts do not pile up.",
  "aboutTabEditorSection2Title": "Relationship to other data",
  "aboutTabEditorSection2Subtitle": "Content being edited and formally saved content have clear boundaries.",
  "aboutTabEditorSection2Item0Title": "Drafts are excluded from search",
  "aboutTabEditorSection2Item0Body": "Search only covers formally saved vault content. Drafts do not appear in results.",
  "aboutTabEditorSection2Item1Title": "Drafts are excluded from full backup",
  "aboutTabEditorSection2Item1Body": "Full backups wrap only the formal vault, not `drafts/`. Backup and restore focus on saved data, not unfinished editing state.",
  "aboutTabEditorSection2Item2Title": "Unsaved indicator",
  "aboutTabEditorSection2Item2Body": "If an entry still has a local draft, list and view modes show an unsaved marker reminding you that content is not formally saved yet.",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreLabel": "Backup and restore",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreHeroTitle": "Keep the whole vault or export readable content",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreHeroBody": "Backup and export both move data out, but for different purposes. Full backup preserves the entire encrypted vault. Markdown and HTML turn content into readable, organizable, re-importable formats. Do not mix the two flows.",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreChip0": "Full encrypted backup",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreChip1": "Google Drive",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreChip2": "Markdown",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreChip3": "HTML",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection0Title": "When full backup fits",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection0Subtitle": "If you want to preserve the entire formal vault and restore it later as-is, use full backup.",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection0Item0Title": "Preserve the entire encrypted vault",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection0Item0Body": "`backup_*.zip` wraps formal data in `vault/`, including entries, attachments, recovery settings, and tag directories. Content stays encrypted, not plaintext.",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection0Item1Title": "Verified after creation",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection0Item1Body": "Full backups are structurally verified before delivery to local storage, external folders, or Google Drive.",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection0Item2Title": "Retention count",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection0Item2Body": "Local backups and Google Drive keep the latest {retainCount} copies. Exports to external folders are not automatically rotated or deleted.",
  "@aboutTabBackupRestoreSection0Item2Body": {
    "placeholders": {
      "retainCount": {
        "type": "int"
      }
    }
  },
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection1Title": "What happens during restore",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection1Subtitle": "Restore does not patch missing entries. It replaces the current formal vault with the backup copy.",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection1Item0Title": "The formal vault is overwritten",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection1Item0Body": "Whether from the in-app list or an external zip, restore overwrites the current `vault/` with backup contents.",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection1Item1Title": "The search index is rebuilt",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection1Item1Body": "During restore, the existing index is deleted and rebuilt from the new formal data. Re-verification may be required if trusted status cannot carry over.",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection1Item2Title": "Recovery key may be required",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection1Item2Body": "If trusted status on this device cannot directly match that backup, the flow asks for the recovery key saved when the backup was created.",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection2Title": "When import and export fit",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection2Subtitle": "This flow handles content exchange and reading, not replacing the entire vault.",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection2Item0Title": "Import",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection2Item0Body": "Import from zip, Markdown, HTML, or folders. For zip files, the system first checks whether the backup format is supported.",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection2Item1Title": "Export",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection2Item1Body": "Export `markdown_*.zip` from Settings, or export `html_*.html` from selected entries or overview on the home screen for readable formats.",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection2Item2Title": "It is not a sync service",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection2Item2Body": "Google Drive here is an optional encrypted backup destination, not a cross-device real-time diary sync service.",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection3Title": "Things to know before use",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection3Subtitle": "Backup and export both matter, but they protect different things with different responsibility boundaries.",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection3Item0Title": "Full backup excludes drafts",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection3Item0Body": "Full backup covers only the formal vault, not `drafts/`. Content still being edited and not formally saved is not included.",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection3Item1Title": "Protect readable exports yourself",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection3Item1Body": "Markdown and HTML exports are for reading, organizing, and moving content, but they are no longer in-app encrypted formats. You decide how to store them afterward.",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection3Item2Title": "Do not mix the two flows",
  "aboutTabBackupRestoreSection3Item2Body": "Use full backup if you want to restore the entire vault later. Use Markdown or HTML export if you want to read or organize content outside the app."
}
